<br>
&gt; When approaching enemy territory is it better to 1) run at full speed<br>
&gt; to get where you are going as fast as possible OR 2) move cautiously<br>
&gt; through trees and undergrowth (risking getting separated from the group)?<br>
<br>
This depends on the situation. If there is already a heated battle taking place and you are in a hurry to join it then use the direct method.<br>
<br>
If you are in a small group and are not sure what is going on, definitely use trees and such so you do not get surprised and insta-smashed.<br>
<br>
&gt; Is there any way to &quot;detect&quot; hidden or stealthy snipers?<br>
<br>
Basically this is a factor of your level (or stealth skill if you have it) versus their stealth skill.<br>
<br>
&gt; Is there any way of readily identifying the enemy at a distance other than<br>
&gt; individually selecting them and reading their stats?<br>
<br>
Nope.<br>
<br>
What class specific tips can be offered to us up-coming members?<br>
<br>
&gt; What should we be specializing in and developing in andicipation of RvR?<br>
&gt; e.g for a Skald is there any advantage to using Sword over Axe or Hammer<br>
<br>
No difference between weapons really. Hammers are nice versus plate, but its not a big deal really. As a skald I would say always max battlesongs.<br>
<br>
&gt; For Healers - what are the most advantageous spells and strategies? <br>
<br>
Don't get too obsessed with pacification. In the long run, you want good mending also (and some aug).<br>
<br>
My #1 piece of advice for healers in RvR: RE-READ THE NAME OF YOUR CLASS. Your primary duty is HEALING. Heal the tanks. Heal the casters. Do as much mez/stunning as you can, but also HEAL. A tank that you heal a few times is like having 2 tanks. Same with a caster!<br>
<br>
&gt; For casters is it better to use DeBuff spells over DD spells? <br>
<br>
Both.<br>
 <p>-Glamis Askamelodi, Thane of Thor<BR>
http://www.threshold-rpg.com</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4F4F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ulordcindrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lord Cindrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Councellor</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/18/01 4:32:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=178.topic&index=7>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Basic Strategy for RvR</span><hr size=1> My main RvR tips:<br>
<br>
1) Learn the frontier<br>
<br>
2) Stay with your group<br>
<br>
3) Follow the instructions of your party, raid, etc. leader<br>
<br>
4) Healers heal and stun. Don't melee unless its absolutely necessary (or small group). <br>
<br>
5) Tanks attack in groups, don't run into a mob solo. Don't let someone drag you into a mob because you are /stuck to them.<br>
<br>
6) Focus on killing casters, rezzers, and snipers.<br>
<br>
7) DO NOT CHASE people too close to their keeps and aggro the npc guards.<br>
<br>
8 )  If you have information to give, make sure its accurate. Don't say &quot;lots of hibs&quot; or &quot;tons of albs&quot;. Get a decent estimate. Always overestimate the numbers. If you see 10, there are probably at least 15-20. If you see 6, there are probably 8-10. It is really horrible when someone says &quot;6-8 Albs at AG&quot;, and you show up with your group of 10 and there are actually 20 there. Don't say &quot;albs here&quot;, say where they are. Don't say &quot;I am dead&quot;, say where you are dead. Don't say &quot;I just got sniped&quot;, say where you got sniped. Provide accurate and valuable information all at the same time. Don't spread it out over multiple tells.<br>
<br>
 <p>-Glamis Askamelodi, Thane of Thor<BR>
