           -- Gisli<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=torveigmaclear>Torveig MacLear</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Captain of The Black Watch</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/19/01 6:34:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=178.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Basic Strategy for RvR</span><hr size=1> I've got some tips for ye.  <br>
<br>
- Don't charge into the middle of the enemy.  Ye're likely to get surrounded and beat from all sides.  A quick and glorious death but it certainly is not nearly as glorious as cleaving the enemy and surviving!<br>
<br>
- It is sometimes effective to act like you are going to charge into the enemies ranks and turn quickly at the edge of their ranks and sprint back into the middle of your own ranks.  Some newer RvR folks on the enemy side may make the mistake of /sticking to you and winding up in the middle of your ranks.  It's death to them if they do.<br>
<br>
- Stun.  Root.  Mez.  Stun.  Root.  Mez.  I can't say it enough.  As a meleer meself, I know that it's an effective tactic when them dastardly elves use it on me.  Use it on them, I say!  Keep that up enough and have some meleers or some blasters around and the elves will be butchered in no time.<br>
<br>
- Don't get caught alone.  If so, you are meat waiting to be butchered when you get rooted.  You have no one to heal you and no one to defend you if you are away from the group.  You're only chance in RvR is with a group.  It's blind luck if you happen to find someone that you can kill while away from the group.  Blind luck works some of the time.  A good group works most of the time.<br>
<br>
- Don't panic.  Decide what you are going to do before you charge into battle and stick to it.  As long as you are focused on your plan you won't panic.  Panic will kill you faster than any elf.<br>
<br>
- Use your healer if you have one.  Send tells to your healer letting him/her know when you need a heal.  Often healers get so busy in RvR they don't see who needs healing.  Sending a tell is a way to remind them that you are there and need some help.<br>
<br>
- Related to the above tip: KEEP YOUR HEALER ALIVE.  Meleers keep an eye on the healer and don't let them get killed.  If you are a healer, stay out of the thick of things.  Stay close enough to mez and heal but far enough away to avoid damage to yourself.  If you die, the clan has lost more than one warrior.  It's lost all the healing and ressing you could be doing if you were alive.  It's a very large strategic loss to lose a healer.<br>
<br>
- Find points of strategic focus.  This means kills the enemies healers, casters and singers.  This kills their buffs, deletes mezzes, removes their ability to heal and do massive AoE damage.  After that is done, cleaning up the meleers is cake.<br>
<br>
- Agonisties and Glamis are two of the most effective Lear battle leaders I have seen so far.  They are also known to others outside our clan.  If they tell you to do something in RvR, do it immediately.  <br>
<br>
- Communicate all the time.  Make sure others know what you are doing and why.  90% of communication is listening.  Make sure you read what is going on in chat and know what your part is to play.<br>
<br>
- Probably the most important part of RvR (kind of our Primary Directive): THE DEFENSE OF OUR HOMELANDS IS PRIORITY ABOVE ALL ELSE.  Imagine living in a realm where the enemy takes and hold portions of your land almost 100% of the time.  That would be Albion and Hibernia.  Shame to them.  May their fathers forget their faces.<br>
<br>
