t one point, I was at Dun Crucheon with 5 members in a group, and we heard that we had a decent force coming out of the TP fort to engage them.  I figured that the broken remnants of the Albion force would be running south down the road at any minute, so I brought my group out to catch them.  We went up the road, no Albions.  We approached the milegate from the Albion side, no Albions except maybe one or two on the wall.  We charged through the gate and completely surprised two that we cut down.  A moment later, bunch of Albions were heading our way all of a sudden from the direction of our TP fort.  We put up a good stand, but got overwhelmed.  30 seconds later, our victorious troops arrived, completely destroying the Albion force.  I was told that the Albions turned to meet our charge in their rear, at which point the main force broke them from what was now their back.<br>
